what data you're collecting

00:00:48.970 --> 00:00:51.950
and how you're using it, is
very important to be shared.

00:00:51.950 --> 00:00:53.830
SEB GRUBB: So, to ensure
Android can continue

00:00:53.830 --> 00:00:56.300
to serve as a platform that
allows developers to build

00:00:56.300 --> 00:00:58.690
such experiences
and protect users,

00:00:58.690 --> 00:01:02.730
we have ongoing efforts
that span multiple releases.

00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:05.370
So the things we want to
touch upon today are--

00:01:05.370 --> 00:01:07.590
how your apps are
accessing user data;

00:01:07.590 --> 00:01:09.480
ensuring that your
users have control

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:12.330
over data being accessed;
and, most importantly,

00:01:12.330 --> 00:01:15.060
that there is transparency
into why the data is required

00:01:15.060 --> 00:01:18.090
and how it is being used.

00:01:18.090 --> 00:01:21.290
So we have a multilayered
approach to privacy in Android.

00:01:21.290 --> 00:01:23.510
Firstly, we focus
on platform updates

00:01:23.510 --> 00:01:26.270
to improve the APIs that
are used by apps to access

00:01:26.270 --> 00:01:28.440
personal information.

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:30.450
PARUL SOI: We then set
up our Play policies

00:01:30.450 --> 00:01:33.210
for keeping abuse in
check and also ensuring

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:35.040
that a level playing
field is provided

00:01:35.040 --> 00:01:39.050
to the developers and a safe
experience for our users.

00:01:39.050 --> 00:01:41.020
SEB GRUBB: We've built
out a [INAUDIBLE] layer

00:01:41.020 --> 00:01:43.920
to identify early on
when apps may be abusing

00:01:43.920 --> 00:01:47.440
a user's personal information.

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:49.370
PARUL SOI: We also
have human reviewers

00:01:49.370 --> 00:01:52.300
so it's not just bots and
AI, but actual people who

00:01:52.300 --> 00:01:55.720
review these apps to make sure
that a user's right to privacy

00:01:55.720 --> 00:01:59.720
