was being contacted,

00:06:39.270 --> 00:06:41.450
allowing other apps
to glean information

00:06:41.450 --> 00:06:44.960
about interactions not happening
within their own scope.

00:06:44.960 --> 00:06:47.600
So, as of January next
year, a limited set

00:06:47.600 --> 00:06:50.930
of contact fields and methods
will be made obsolete.

00:06:50.930 --> 00:06:53.570
These include fields relating
to the last time a contact was

00:06:53.570 --> 00:06:55.690
accessed or contacted.

00:06:55.690 --> 00:06:58.700
So if your app is accessing
or updating these fields,

00:06:58.700 --> 00:07:00.810
we ask you to use
alternative methods.

00:07:00.810 --> 00:07:03.760
For example, you could
fulfill certain use cases

00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:05.325
by using private
content providers

00:07:05.325 --> 00:07:07.325
or simply storing data
in your back-end systems.

